HB 4036-2
(LC 209)
2/2/26 (RLM/ps)
Requested by HOUSE COMMITTEE ON HOUSING AND HOMELESSNESS (at the request of Rep-
resentative Pam Marsh)
PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
HOUSE BILL 4036
1 On page 1 of the printed bill, delete lines 7 through 27.
2 On page 2, delete lines 1 and 2 and insert:
3 “SECTION 2. (1) The Housing Opportunity, Longevity and Durabil-
4 ity Fund is established in the State Treasury, separate and distinct
5 from the General Fund. Interest earned on moneys in the Housing
6 Opportunity, Longevity and Durability Fund shall be credited to the
7 fund.
8 “(2) The fund consists of moneys deposited into the fund from bonds
9 issued by the State Treasurer pursuant to ORS 286A.035 for the Hous-
10 ing and Community Services Department to be used for affordable
11 housing preservation.
12 “(3) Moneys in the fund are continuously appropriated to the de-
13 partment to:
14 “(a) Acquire, construct, remodel, repair, equip or furnish affordable
15 housing at risk of loss, as described in ORS 456.824 (2), that is or will
16 be owned or operated, as those terms are defined in ORS 458.480, by
17 the State of Oregon for the purpose of providing affordable housing;
18 “(b) Pay the costs incurred by the department to administer the
19 fund; and
20 “(c) Pay bond-related costs, as defined in ORS 286A.816.
21 “SECTION 3. On or before December 1, 2026, the Housing and

1 Community Services Department shall submit a report in the manner
2 provided by ORS 192.245 to the interim committees of the Legislative
3 Assembly related to housing that incorporates feedback from key
4 stakeholders, including affordable housing providers, finance entities
5 and tenant advocates, and that:
6 “(1) Evaluates the impact of and offers improvements to any state
7 laws or practices, policies or rules of the department that negatively
8 impact the efficiency, effectiveness and cost of operating affordable
9 housing, including impacts to leasing, screening applicants, filling va-
10 cancies, maintaining tenant wait lists, recertifying tenants, conduct-
11 ing inspections, collecting rent, managing property and complying
12 with regulations; and
13 “(2) Evaluates opportunities to streamline, reduce or eliminate re-
14 porting requirements of affordable housing providers for state and
15 federal programs and funding sources that are administered by the
16 department.”.
17 In line 14, delete “physical or financial distress” and insert “financial or
18 physical distress, including physical distress that requires rehabilitation, re-
19 pair or replacement of such building systems, components or materials that
20 have exceeded, or within a reasonable period will exceed, their effective
21 useful lives”.
22 On page 3, delete line 45.
23 On page 4, delete line 1 and insert:
24 (D) Housing Opportunity,
25 Longevity and Durability
26 Fund..................................................... $100,000,000
27 On page 7, delete line 23 and insert:
28 Bonds.............................................. $ 2,440,290,000
